136
00:08:33.045 --> 00:08:35.014  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
This is a war.

137
00:08:38.784 --> 00:08:41.220  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I-- I can't go along with this.

138
00:08:41.287 --> 00:08:43.890  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You can't just pull out now.

139
00:08:44.557 --> 00:08:47.293  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Desertion is a serious violation
of the rules.

140
00:08:47.793 --> 00:08:49.562  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Then what are you gonna do about it?!

141
00:08:49.695 --> 00:08:51.864  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You gonna lock every one of us up?!

142
00:08:52.532 --> 00:08:53.232  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Let's see...

143
00:08:57.870 --> 00:08:58.738  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Mr. Sato...

144
00:08:59.138 --> 00:09:00.072  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
What are you doing?

145
00:09:00.740 --> 00:09:04.544  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
If I felt like it, I could cut off
all your heads.

146
00:09:05.211 --> 00:09:06.579  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Mr. Sato...

147
00:09:07.647 --> 00:09:08.748  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Why?

148
00:09:10.016 --> 00:09:11.017  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Finally...

149
00:09:11.951 --> 00:09:14.120  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Finally Japan is listening to us!

150
00:09:14.820 --> 00:09:19.725  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
We've worked so hard for that,
for a future for Ajin...

151
00:09:19.792 --> 00:09:22.695  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I don't care about any of that.

152
00:09:23.162 --> 00:09:26.832  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
All I care about is excitement.

153
00:09:27.066 --> 00:09:29.869  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
That's what we're fighting for.

154
00:09:32.204 --> 00:09:33.306  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Mr. Sato...

155
00:09:34.807 --> 00:09:36.709  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You're out of your mind...

156
00:09:37.877 --> 00:09:38.978  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[chuckles]

157
00:09:41.647 --> 00:09:42.848  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
AJIN SATO BOMBS PRIME MINISTER'S RESIDENCE

158
00:09:42.915 --> 00:09:45.151  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
<i>The area within a 1-kilometer radius</i>
<i>of the Prime Minister's residence</i>

159
00:09:45.217 --> 00:09:47.186  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
<i>is currently closed off</i>

160
00:09:47.253 --> 00:09:50.156  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
<i>as the chemical protection unit</i>
<i>continues to work tirelessly!</i>

161
00:09:50.222 --> 00:09:51.757  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[crowd] This is seriously bad!

162
00:09:51.824 --> 00:09:53.659  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Where can we run?!

163
00:09:53.893 --> 00:09:56.796  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>The government has ordered citizens</i>
<i>to seek shelter indoors.</i>

164
00:10:05.805 --> 00:10:07.239  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You guys go on ahead.

165
00:10:07.907 --> 00:10:09.141  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I'll keep a lookout behind.

166
00:10:13.713 --> 00:10:16.682  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Sato's gone completely nuts...

167
00:10:27.893 --> 00:10:30.630  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Okuyama, you okay with this?

168
00:10:30.696 --> 00:10:33.232  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
There's no point in playing war games
forever.

169
00:10:34.767 --> 00:10:37.370  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
But what'll we do now?

170
00:10:38.170 --> 00:10:42.074  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
This won't go down well
if Sato catches us...

171
00:10:43.075 --> 00:10:44.677  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I have an idea about that.

172
00:10:53.319 --> 00:10:55.287  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>As unrest continues to grip the country,</i>

173
00:10:55.821 --> 00:10:59.291  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>some people are turning violent</i>
<i>and incidents of attacks on the family</i>

174
00:10:59.425 --> 00:11:02.962  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>of Ajin have been occurring under</i>
<i>the pretext of so-called Ajin hunts.</i>

175
00:11:04.130 --> 00:11:05.297  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
AJIN HUNTERS ATTACK FAMILIES OF AJIN

176
00:11:05.364 --> 00:11:08.267  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
<i>The families of the Ajin Tanaka and Nagai</i>
<i>are already under protection,</i>

177
00:11:08.334 --> 00:11:10.870  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
<i>but the status of Kei Nagai's</i>
<i>younger sister is unknown.</i>

178
00:11:10.936 --> 00:11:11.804  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
NAGAI ERIKO (14)

179
00:11:11.871 --> 00:11:15.708  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>There are reports that rioters have</i>
<i>mobbed the facility she is hospitalized.</i>

180
00:11:22.882 --> 00:11:24.450  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[crowd] Where's Nagai's sister?

181
00:11:24.717 --> 00:11:26.185  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Where is she?!

182
00:11:26.252 --> 00:11:28.320  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-Stop this!
-Calm down!

183
00:11:29.088 --> 00:11:30.756  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-Where is she?
-She isn't here!

184
00:11:30.823 --> 00:11:31.690  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Find her!

185
00:11:39.965 --> 00:11:41.700  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[muffled screaming]

186
00:11:42.234 --> 00:11:43.102  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Eri!

187
00:11:45.037 --> 00:11:46.038  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
K-- Kei?

188
00:11:46.105 --> 00:11:47.406  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Let's go, Eri.

189
00:11:47.740 --> 00:11:48.908  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Don't touch me!

190
00:11:50.242 --> 00:11:51.277  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Whose fault is this?!

191
00:11:52.111 --> 00:11:54.413  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Who do you think got me into this mess?!

192
00:11:54.480 --> 00:11:56.082  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Idiot, be quiet!

193
00:11:56.148 --> 00:11:57.016  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Stop it!

194
00:11:57.416 --> 00:11:58.350  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
What are you doing?!

195
00:11:58.818 --> 00:12:00.753  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-Why did you come here?!
-There she is!

196
00:12:01.854 --> 00:12:02.855  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Hey, isn't that--

197
00:12:02.988 --> 00:12:04.090  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
It's Nagai!

198
00:12:04.156 --> 00:12:05.157  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
It's Kei Nagai!

199
00:12:05.224 --> 00:12:06.158  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Hurry!

200
00:12:06.826 --> 00:12:07.893  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>Should I use my voice?!</i>

201
00:12:08.227 --> 00:12:10.362  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>But then even Eri</i>
<i>won't be able to move...</i>

202
00:12:16.001 --> 00:12:17.503  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Hey! Got him!

203
00:12:21.140 --> 00:12:22.741  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Serves you right!

204
00:12:22.808 --> 00:12:23.943  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Let's do this!

205
00:12:24.243 --> 00:12:25.744  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
The Ajin hunt is on!

206
00:12:26.912 --> 00:12:27.980  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[Eri] N-- No!

207
00:12:30.449 --> 00:12:31.317  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Kei?

208
00:12:32.751 --> 00:12:33.486  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[Nagai] <i>Come out!</i>

209
00:12:34.487 --> 00:12:36.222  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>Ghost!</i>

210
00:12:38.824 --> 00:12:39.992  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[gasps]

211
00:12:53.439 --> 00:12:55.141  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-Kai!..
-Come on!

212
00:12:55.774 --> 00:12:57.309  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Damn it, this is bad.

213
00:13:19.932 --> 00:13:22.268  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Are you feeling better now?

214
00:13:26.839 --> 00:13:27.506  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Then let's go.

215
00:13:28.541 --> 00:13:31.443  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I can't go all the way to the police,
but I can take you close.

216
00:13:32.178 --> 00:13:33.279  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-But--
-Wait.

217
00:13:35.548 --> 00:13:36.415  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Kei.

218
00:13:37.550 --> 00:13:38.851  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Run with us.

219
00:13:39.418 --> 00:13:40.286  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Kai.

220
00:13:41.453 --> 00:13:42.555  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I saw it on the news.

221
00:13:43.155 --> 00:13:44.456  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
It's been rough, right?

222
00:13:44.857 --> 00:13:46.926  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-'Cause of that Sato guy.
-So?

223
00:13:47.459 --> 00:13:49.061  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
It has nothing to do with you.

224
00:13:49.128 --> 00:13:50.196  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Hey, Kei!

225
00:13:50.563 --> 00:13:51.864  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Shut up, Eri.

226
00:13:51.931 --> 00:13:53.966  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
But you shouldn't talk to Kai like--

227
00:13:54.033 --> 00:13:54.900  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Shut up.

228
00:13:56.302 --> 00:13:59.972  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
With his connections,
we can escape to India.

229
00:14:01.473 --> 00:14:03.409  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
This time let's really escape together.

230
00:14:03.909 --> 00:14:06.445  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You're still saying that?

231
00:14:07.213 --> 00:14:08.113  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
What's wrong?

232
00:14:09.215 --> 00:14:12.952  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I'm not the same as I was before.

233
00:14:14.853 --> 00:14:16.889  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
No matter what I do,
I keep having to fight,

234
00:14:18.023 --> 00:14:20.192  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
and so many people have died
before my eyes.

235
00:14:21.093 --> 00:14:22.361  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
It's become clear to me now.

236
00:14:24.363 --> 00:14:26.432  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I don't need any unnecessary feelings.

237
00:14:27.433 --> 00:14:29.568  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
It's stupid to get carried away
by emotion.

238
00:14:29.635 --> 00:14:32.504  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-Kei...
-Don't you get it, Kai?!

239
00:14:33.072 --> 00:14:35.307  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You saved me, and I abandoned you!

240
00:14:35.608 --> 00:14:38.277  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
You got thrown into juvenile hall
because of me!

241
00:14:39.411 --> 00:14:41.247  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-I guess.
-So just...

242
00:14:41.914 --> 00:14:43.449  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
So just leave me alone!

243
00:14:44.316 --> 00:14:45.451  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
But we're friends, right?

244
00:14:48.354 --> 00:14:49.521  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You're my friend, Kei.

245
00:14:54.093 --> 00:14:57.997  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You really still think that.

246
00:14:58.664 --> 00:14:59.565  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Of course I do.

247
00:15:01.934 --> 00:15:03.269  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You really haven't changed...

248
00:15:05.371 --> 00:15:09.942  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
You haven't changed
since we were kids, Kai...

249
00:15:10.976 --> 00:15:11.644  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
That so?

250
00:15:19.084 --> 00:15:19.952  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Thank you.

251
00:15:20.586 --> 00:15:24.056  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Okay, so it's decided.
We'll go ahead with the plan.

252
00:15:43.943 --> 00:15:46.145  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
That guy's an idiot, huh?

253
00:15:47.413 --> 00:15:50.115  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Yeah, he is.

254
00:15:51.083 --> 00:15:52.251  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
He's such an idiot.

255
00:15:53.085 --> 00:15:55.454  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
He said you'd definitely
go to your sister...

256
00:15:56.488 --> 00:15:58.223  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
so we had to go rescue you.

257
00:15:59.291 --> 00:16:00.392  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Insisted on it.

258
00:16:02.061 --> 00:16:03.595  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Even though you abandoned him.

259
00:16:12.604 --> 00:16:14.106  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Yeah.

260
00:16:15.140 --> 00:16:16.575  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
There's something wrong with him.

261
00:16:16.642 --> 00:16:19.511  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-Ah? You--
-All I've ever done

262
00:16:19.745 --> 00:16:21.480  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
is try to be a successful person.

263
00:16:22.281 --> 00:16:26.518  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
And I've chosen only what I needed
to that end.

264
00:16:27.753 --> 00:16:28.620  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
And yet...

265
00:16:30.622 --> 00:16:36.328  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
And yet that weirdo was my only friend.

266
00:16:39.531 --> 00:16:41.734  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[scoffs] What's up with that?

267
00:16:44.670 --> 00:16:47.639  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Can I ask you a favor?

268
00:17:00.552 --> 00:17:03.022  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Eri, I'm sorry.

269
00:17:05.691 --> 00:17:09.428  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
You went through a lot of trouble
because of me.

270
00:17:10.696 --> 00:17:12.564  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
What's all this, all of the sudden...?

271
00:17:12.631 --> 00:17:13.499  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I'm really sorry.

272
00:17:14.800 --> 00:17:16.035  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Whatever. It's fine...

273
00:17:16.101 --> 00:17:18.237  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
But at least when you're running away,
be quiet.

274
00:17:18.404 --> 00:17:19.805  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
It was stupid to yell like that.

275
00:17:20.339 --> 00:17:22.474  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
That was because you showed up
out of nowhere.

276
00:17:26.712 --> 00:17:29.448  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-Uh, Kai.
-What is it?

277
00:17:29.515 --> 00:17:31.450  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Sorry to ask at a time like this...

278
00:17:33.185 --> 00:17:35.687  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
but I've really gotta pee.

279
00:17:36.155 --> 00:17:38.757  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Ah. Okay, I'll stop on the side.

280
00:17:47.433 --> 00:17:48.700  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Kei's taking a long time.

281
00:17:52.337 --> 00:17:53.405  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I'm gonna check on him.

282
00:17:53.772 --> 00:17:54.673  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
There's no point.

283
00:17:55.407 --> 00:17:56.508  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
That's a long piss.

284
00:17:58.677 --> 00:18:00.779  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
He asked you to take care of his sister.

285
00:18:02.347 --> 00:18:03.382  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
What do you mean...?!

286
00:18:03.782 --> 00:18:04.650  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Kei.

287
00:18:05.317 --> 00:18:10.222  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
You're an idiot,
but your friend's an idiot too.

288
00:18:11.557 --> 00:18:12.424  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Shut up.

289
00:18:14.693 --> 00:18:15.861  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
He's not an idiot.

290
00:18:31.443 --> 00:18:32.778  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[humming]

291
00:18:36.381 --> 00:18:38.383  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You sure seem to be having fun.

292
00:18:38.884 --> 00:18:41.854  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Are those games really that fun?

293
00:18:44.456 --> 00:18:45.457  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Yeah.

294
00:18:45.757 --> 00:18:50.395  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
The higher the difficulty, the greater
the satisfaction when you clear it.

295
00:18:51.663 --> 00:18:54.233  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Did you do it on purpose?

296
00:18:56.368 --> 00:18:58.504  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Did you set it up so they'd betray you?

297
00:18:59.138 --> 00:19:02.541  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
[laughs] You say the funniest things,
Tanaka.

298
00:19:03.175 --> 00:19:06.712  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Did you think that would make
your game more fun?

299
00:19:07.346 --> 00:19:10.182  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Well, it's true that the fewer allies
you have

300
00:19:10.449 --> 00:19:13.218  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
the more people you can kill yourself.

301
00:19:17.723 --> 00:19:18.724  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Mr. Sato,

302
00:19:19.791 --> 00:19:21.393  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
you really are a fool.

303
00:19:22.461 --> 00:19:24.696  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
You're not the person
I thought you were,

304
00:19:25.197 --> 00:19:27.799  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
and I have no clue what you're
thinking.

305
00:19:28.767 --> 00:19:29.635  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
But...

306
00:19:30.469 --> 00:19:31.603  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[gasps

307
00:19:35.374 --> 00:19:37.376  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
The Player 2 slot is open.

308
00:19:38.577 --> 00:19:40.179  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[chuckles]

309
00:19:43.849 --> 00:19:45.250  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[groaning]

310
00:19:46.218 --> 00:19:49.221  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Mr. Tosaki,
maybe you should rest a little...

311
00:19:49.288 --> 00:19:49.955  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I'm fine.

312
00:19:51.390 --> 00:19:52.824  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[sighs]

313
00:20:01.633 --> 00:20:05.637  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I never thought you'd attack a tank
with a spear.

314
00:20:05.704 --> 00:20:07.372  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
There's nothing else
we can do...

315
00:20:08.874 --> 00:20:10.709  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Just like Don Quixote.

316
00:20:18.350 --> 00:20:19.518  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Nagai!

317
00:20:22.254 --> 00:20:23.455  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[Tosaki] Why did you come back?

318
00:20:24.456 --> 00:20:25.490  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
It should be obvious.

319
00:20:26.592 --> 00:20:30.896  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You need my help to stop Sato.

320
00:20:31.430 --> 00:20:32.431  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Don't make me laugh!

321
00:20:32.831 --> 00:20:33.699  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Mr. Tosaki!

322
00:20:33.999 --> 00:20:35.801  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Just what can you do for us now?!

323
00:20:35.867 --> 00:20:42.274  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I know that you don't trust me,
and I don't care.

324
00:20:43.775 --> 00:20:44.676  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
But...

325
00:20:47.579 --> 00:20:49.548  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I'm going to stop Sato.

326
00:20:50.315 --> 00:20:51.717  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Because that's what I should do.

327
00:20:59.291 --> 00:21:00.259  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[man] Target confirmed.

328
00:21:01.326 --> 00:21:01.994  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Breach.

329
00:21:15.507 --> 00:21:16.408  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
It's a trap!

330
00:21:22.981 --> 00:21:25.550  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
To be continued

331
00:21:26.718 --> 00:21:29.755  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
[chorus singing]
<i>I'm tired of this one already, so</i>

332
00:21:29.821 --> 00:21:33.025  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>I'll trade it</i>

333
00:21:33.292 --> 00:21:38.430  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>For your ordinary one</i>

334
00:21:39.564 --> 00:21:45.771  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>A shiny holy card</i>

335
00:21:45.871 --> 00:21:51.543  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>For a grainy paper card</i>

336
00:21:52.344 --> 00:21:56.448  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>You can see them all</i>

337
00:21:58.650 --> 00:22:02.988  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>When you come to my house</i>

338
00:22:03.055 --> 00:22:09.094  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>So</i>
<i>Two of us in the corner of the schoolyard</i>

339
00:22:09.361 --> 00:22:11.463  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>While the wind blows</i>

340
00:22:11.530 --> 00:22:15.734  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>I might be able to say it now</i>

341
00:22:17.836 --> 00:22:24.042  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>Words I've never said to anyone</i>

342
00:22:24.109 --> 00:22:30.549  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>"Won't you come and play, I'll be nice"</i>

343
00:22:30.615 --> 00:22:36.521  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>"I'll give you anything, see"</i>

344
00:22:36.988 --> 00:22:39.758  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>"Be my friend</i>

345
00:22:39.825 --> 00:22:46.665  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>Always"</i>

